cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes extensions to a robustness score for deep neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on deep learning and neural networks suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely categories. The discussion of defensive techniques and evaluation of intrinsic robustness suggest cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a possible category. The use of extreme value theory and formal guarantees suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on evaluating neural network robustness suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
